content.detailedDescription: 1.Lying on my back in the yard in the sun with my head in the shade from thehouse, looking at the sky.2.The observation was made while in a relaxed stateand lasted for under 2 seconds. the object simply moved into and out of my fieldof vision.3.My mind rapidly interpreted first a bird, then a plane.4.I expectedto hear some kind of sound as it was apparent the object was not a bird (far toofast). i was amazed to have seen so much detail in such a short period of time.If the object was some order of stealth technology it was utterly silent andsomehow created no atmospheric shock waves at supersonic speed. it did not havewings as it was a thick black triangular object. my reaction was one of mildexcitation following the calm observation.5.It moved in a straight line north tosouth at about 40 degrees to the sw directly through my field of vision. i wouldestimate it to be traveling at an elevation of approximatly 1500 ft. at a speedin excess of 2000 mph.6. i lost sight of the object behind a tree.
content.summary: Fast silent thick black triangle north to south lo

content.detailedDescription: we heard a rumor about someone seeing lights in akind of remote area not to far from us so my cousin and i rode up to the sitewhere the lights were seen and as soon as we arrived we saw a couple of brightlights that were bouncing around in the sky and would stop and go back and thencontinue forward then get to a certain point and then disappear - it looks likewe are seen sitting there watching them and then it will go out - and one nightwe saw an object fly over us in the shape of a triangle with alot of roundlights on the bottom - sounds kind of weird and maybe nothing to investigate butit happens on a nightly basis when the night is clear
content.summary: Flashing lights , bobing around

content.detailedDescription: Hi my name is robbie and it was about 9:00 pm in henderson, nv. i was leaving mymoms house and was starting to head s.W. when i noticed this craft in the air.It seemed like it was about 700 feet in the air and it was moving very slow wheni 1st saw it then when i got closer it stopped in the air and hovered. it wasnot a blimp and there was no sound so i know it was not a helicopter. it hadlights going around the bottom of it. i called my mom who was only about 1/2mile from where i was at the time i noticed the craft. she went into herbackyard and confirmed that she was watching it and described it exactly the wayim describing it now. i had to drive past it to go to work but she watched itfor about 10 minutes and she told me that it just continued to hover. shefinally got bored and went into the house. thank you
content.summary: Circular--stationary in air with lights on bottom-

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting in my solarium looking eastward.The object came out from behindthe building across the street - level of the 8th story.A child balloon.Interest- this is not the first time.The object floated south for appro.500 ft, turnedeastward and started climbing steadily.  all the while, it kept flickering -dull surface to mirror surface.The sky was perfect.  suddenly a huge cloudformed over a distance of about 20 miles and came to pick up the sphere.  at theprecise moment, i could not seen more since the sun bounced back on the biggerobject and my eyes were watering from the light.  the whole incident lasted over10 minutes.
content.summary: Metallic sphere picked up by quick moving cumulus

content.detailedDescription: Witness work is related to the medical profession.  she works nights, gets homeabout 12:30 a.M., and stays up sometimes as late as 6:00 a.M.In early morning hours of january 22, 2002, as witness was lying across hersisters bed (facing east) talking long distance with her boyfriend, a lightshone in the bedroom window and drew her attention to an object hovered above a30-foot utility pole in the back yard some 100 feet from the house and sheestimates that it was hovered at about twice the height of the pole, i.E. about30 feet above the pole, directly east of the bedroom windows.Witness saw 3 white lights, very bright, plus one red light in the center ofwhat seemed to be the underside of the object.  while witness boyfriend waitedon the telephone line, she scrambled to get her glasses and when she againturned toward the window, she realized the object had moved away from theutility pole area.  and when she looked to the northeast, she saw that it washovering again, but now at some distance (perhaps a few miles) away, seeming tohave elevated in altitude.  (at no time, did the witness actually see the objecttravel.)her first impression (based on the positioning of the lights led her to thinkthe object might be triangular, but she was not sure, since the lights when somedistance away did not show the same configuration as she thought them to be upclose (and without her glasses on).The entire episode lasted for perhaps 3 minutes, with the very close, but verybrief sighting of perhaps ten (10) seconds or less near the house furnishing themost clarity for the witness perception - even given the fact that she was notwearing her glasses.Note:  it should be noted that witness at age 18 and on her way home from a highschool dance, saw steady red lights (lower than a jet liner flies) which movedback and forth...And when she pulled in to her home driveway, she stood andlooked for 3-4 minutes before it moved away.Note:  it should also be noted that witness (in a telephone conversation withinvestigator trout) referred briefly to recalling some sort of sightingexperience when she was a child and in the car with her parents, but couldntrecall detail.
content.summary: Lighted object hover back yard 30 ft above utility

content.detailedDescription: onchristmas day night at 6:42 p.M. the family of witnesses (mother, father, and 4children - 2 of whom were toddlers, and the older two children being age 11 and12) were on their way from sioux city, iowa back to omaha, nebraska on i-29(southbound) when south of missouri valley, iowa (about 3 miles north of thenorth omaha exit, which turns west on i-680), they sighted a lighted objectabout one-half mile ahead of their vehicle.The mother called the familys attention to the light ahead of them, commentthat the lights looked like a crown.  it was at first thought that the objectwas an airliner on approach to eppley airfield several miles south of theirposition.  but as the vehicle neared the lights, the family realized that theobject was hovered beside the opposite side of the interstate, rather thanmoving, and realized they were looking at what appeared to be a ufo.They also observed that traffic on the opposite (northbound) side of theinterstate had drastically slowed and that 4 cars had stopped as if observingthe object and that one individual had gotten out of a vehicle and was lookingup at the object.At closest approach, the object was perhaps 500-600 feet ahead and diagonally tothe left (se) of the witnesses vehicle and at an estimated 500 feet altitude. as witnesses vehicle drew near, the object suddenly began to rise, and as itdid so, the witnesses perception was that the objects lights seemed to flip360 degrees (briefly disappearing from view as it flipped, then reappearing intheir original position) as it rose straight up into the clouds and disappeared.Note:  it should be noted that altitude estimates are always subject to thewitness perception.  because of the 2,200 foot cloud ceiling, we at least knowthe object was below 2,200 feet altitude - and the object may in fact have beenno higher than the witness estimate of 500 feet.  without the ability to be morespecific, what seems obvious is that the sighting was close, and at fairly lowaltitude.Sighting duration was perhaps 3-4 minutes.  to the witnesses, the size of theobject was indeterminate - they indicated that it was smaller than an airliner. the adult (father) witness is a well-spoken, thoughtful type individual, who didnot try to over-conclude during phone conversations with the investigator beforenor during the on-site interview conducted on february 17, 2002.  the twoadolescent witnesses, ages 11 and 12, are intelligent children, fascinated andamazed by what they saw and articulately willing to share their perception ofthe incident.  the children exhibited nothing giddy or frivolous as theydescribed and drew sketches of their perceptions of what theyd seen.  theysimply entered seriously into the conversation when encouraged to do so, as wedrove to the site and sat parked for 30 minutes viewing the area.
content.summary: Lights hover i-29,backflip as move straight up

content.detailedDescription: In my aircraft, flying from blythe to twenty-nine palms, 7:30am, 8,500 feet, sunbehind us we spotted a white spherical object moving just above the desert flooras a baloon in wind-erratic, up and down about 100 - 200 feet. object then movedon a straight course right to left in front of our flight path (no furthererratic moves). a second object came into view, same path. both stopped, thentraveled straight up at very fast rate of climb, then disappeared. no visiblewings or other familiar, typical shapes, or  exhaust, thrust (visual from heat)distortion.  ascent rate seemed unreal.
content.summary: Saw two unidentified white objects

content.detailedDescription: I was playing with my new sony dsc f707 5 megapixel camera, and trying out afeature that takes 3 shots in 2.8 seconds, where each shot is exposed a littledarker than the previous shot. i was about a block from my home, next to aballfield at an elementary school, and i was aiming the camera at amountainrange in the background. i did not notice anything unusual when i wastaking the pictures. when i returned home 5 minutes later and transferred theimages to my computer, i noticed a strange object on the second frame. when iexamined the 3rd frame, the object was also present, but it had to travel alarge distance in less than a second to appear on the other side of themountain. i have the original pics on my computer and can upload them to you forexamination.
content.summary: Captured ufo on 5 megapixel digital cam by acciden

content.detailedDescription: i was on the top step about to enter into ourhouse when we saw a ligt blink like a shooting star in a zigzag motion a z withone more line to the left, then it vanished. i was in shock. i observe the starsevery night and what i saw was impossible to make sharp angles like that in amatter of seconds.  we couldnt believe it. i just wanted to know if there wereany other sightings besides us.
content.summary: Blinking light that made a z formation on 4/2/02 a

content.detailedDescription: I was watching the leonid meteor shower, and when i looked straight up i thoughti saw a small flock of geese. it was quickly apparent that it was somethingelse, something i have never seen before! it was three glowing, triangularcraft, that seemed to be paused in flight. imeadiately they moved ,in an everincreasing speed (with smooth acceleration) from straight up toward thenortheast. their height appeared steady. they flew in a triangular formation,except(this is the part of the sighting that most amazed me.) one of the craftzig-zaged (danced) between the other two lights,crafts.Enter your narrativedescription hereplease limit your narrative to 500 words (equivalent to 1 typedpage).
content.summary: 3 triangular craft, lights -dancing, and formation

content.detailedDescription: At 9:45 p.M. tuesday april 16, i walked out of a friends house after an eveningmeeting.  i noticed the object immediately.  it was larger than an aircraftwould have been and was just floating in the sky.  it was cylinder shaped withlights that appeared to be whirring around it. the lights were white with someblue and pink in them. i considered i was possibly seeing an airplane at somestrange angle, but observed several aircraft flying over denver at the time andthis was very different.  the lights were more luminous larger and brighter thanother aircraft i observed.  the object was silent, and started to move in onedirection only, and that was straight down.  when i first saw it, it was about40 degrees above eye level, then it floated straight down like it was going toland.  i lost sight of it behind some trees and couldnt see if it landed ornot.  the sighting lasted 1-2 min.  i was trying so hard to observe it, i didnttry to get another witness.  i lost sight of it too fast and there was no time.
content.summary: Saw lighted object drop straight down from the sky

content.detailedDescription: drivin truck at 3:45 am.Amazing bright light.Noquestion a ufo.Amazed been driving at night for 23 years and never seenanything.Large ball of light mabye one mile in diameter going really fast.Itjust went out of sight going super fast.
content.summary: Bright ball and two saucers this year

content.detailedDescription: driving truck 3:45 am.The sky got very bright.Noquestion a ufo.Amazed and excited that i seen it.Went from high to very low infront of me i can describe every detail.Was going fast and straight just wentout of sight like it was going to the ground.Ive been driveing at night for 23yrs.Looking in the sky this is the first year i saw anything.A month before thati saw two flying sausers 100 yards from my house coming home from work at 5:55pm.I saw the show sightings this morning on sci-fi that inspired me to contactyou.Thanks for listning.Bruce
content.summary: Glowing ball of light very close can describe in d

content.detailedDescription: On april 17th and again on april 20th at approximately 3:15 am i witnessed a redstar-appearing light in the western sky. i was simply looking into the stars andnoticed a bright, red light that flashed even brighter twice in same positionand went out. two night later directly overhed, facinf east, a bright, whitelight flased on twice ,then actually moved about two finger widths at armslength towards the north. these were not stars!
content.summary: 2 occasions i saw ufo lights in night sky

content.detailedDescription: Sighting background:i was contacted by the witness at the close of the minnesota mufon meeting indecember 2001, regarding this sighting.  i interviewed her in january of 2002.Witness description:the witness is a 79 year old female.  she is a homemaker and retired bank andmortgage clerk.  she indicates that her health and hearing are ok and her visionis correctable to 20/20 using eyeglasses, which she was wearing at the time ofthe sighting.  she describes her education level as a partial college education. she has extensively followed the ufo phenomenon in the last few years andindicates that she may have had a number of psychic and ufological experiences.Sighting account:the witness was doing some quick household chores on the main floor of her houseat about 10:30 pm.  she was momentarily standing on her back porch, which is onefloor above ground level, facing southeast.  she indicates that she oftenobserves the sky, and at this moment, she looked up and observed a largetriangular object nearly due south in the sky at an elevation of about 50degrees or higher.  the object moved out of her view so she ran into her living room, which has asouth facing window, and attempted to look up at the object.  she was unable tosee it due to the overhang of the roof.  she thus lost sight of the object atthat point.She felt that the total sighting time was under two minutes [cl estimate:probably less than one minute].  object description:she describes the object as being about six times larger than an aircraft wouldappear at that location.  it moved slowly and silently in an east to west path. she did not know the elevation, and thus could not estimate its size, however,its angular size was larger than that of a garage about  blocks away from whereshe stood [cl estimate, angular size would have been at least that of hand atarms length].The object was described as having at least three non-blinking blue lights oneach wing and one at the apex.  the color was described as dark, but notabsolute black.  the motion of the object was slow, smooth and silent.
content.summary: Plymouth mn ce1  triangular object at close proxim

content.detailedDescription: From report writeup:sighting background===================i and the witness are both friends of another mn mufon member.  i was informedof the sighting by this mutual friend, who indicated that it would be ok tocontact the witness.  i contacted and interviewed both witnesses on 27 february,2002.  both witnesses gave full form 1 reports.  the primary witness also wrotehis description of the sighting in an attached writeup.Witness description===================the witnesses are a couple that lives and works in the bloomington area.  theprimary witness is a 25 year old male.  his health, vision and hearing are allexcellent.  the second witness is his girlfriend.  she is 22  years old and hasexcellent health and hearing.  she describes her vision as less than great(somewhat nearsighted).  she was not wearing her glasses at the time of thesighting.  both witnesses indicate that they have had no health changes sincethe sighting.  both witnesses  work at the same place, and both were there atthe time of the sighting.Sighting account================the primary witness had left work to run a quick errand at a nearby store in thesame strip mall where he works.  at about 5:30 pm cst, as he was walking betweenlocations, he looked to the southwest to observe a bright light which appearedto be stationary, about 45 degrees up in the southwestern sky.  he felt that itseemed unusual  not a star or airplane, and was curious about it.  he watchedit for several minutes, as he walked back from his errand.  the light wasbriefly obscured by a building and when it became visible again, he again saw itat the same location.  along with the first light, a second light was nowapproaching on an east to west path, from a location closer to due south.  as he watched, the second light approached the first from the left (east) at asteady rate, and then merged with it.  the first light remained at the samebrightness, and in the same location.  he ran into work to get his girlfriend(the second witness).  they both stepped outside to observe the light, whichremained motionless in the southwestern sky.  they observed it for slightly lessthan a minute more, as it rapidly, faded out and was no longer visible.Object description==================the primary witness described both objects as solid white lights,  which thewitness described as about the brightness of the moon. [it was not clear whatthis meant, and therefore what the actual brightness was.  however bothwitnesses felt that it was brighter than any stars present].   he indicated thatthey had an observable diameter to them.  he also notes that at the end of thesighting, the remaining object faded from view.The second witness described the object (one object only, since the two lightshad merged by this time), as reddish and about the brightness of a star.  shewas not wearing her glasses at that moment, so could not discern any size to theobject.  she observed it suddenly vanish  it just wasnt there.
content.summary: Bloomington, mn - distant nl/ma1 seen by two witne
